reasoning: This falls outside my circle of competence. I know consumer brands, banks, insurance and simple industrials, but the intricacies of algorithms, cloud infrastructure and AI at Google are beyond what I understand well enough to invest. While on the surface GOOG seems to enjoy a moat—dominant market share in search, network effects in advertising and switching costs—there’s insufficient data here for me to assess its durability. Management under Sundar Pichai appears competent, yet I lack insight into their capital allocation choices across R&D and acquisitions. Without fundamentals, balance‐sheet strength or a clear valuation, I can’t determine a margin of safety. The long-term prospects in AI and cloud could be bright, but I’d rather own wonderful businesses I grasp—like Coca-Cola or Apple—at a price I can calculate. In this case, I politely pass, so my signal is neutral with low conviction until I see the numbers.
